mutant: m030_plan_midsegment_cut_reports_segment_maxseq
target: internal/manifest/plan.go
failure-mode: |
  A mid-segment block-mode truncation sets the continuation cursor from the
  enclosing segment's MaxSeq (seg.Header.MaxSeq) instead of the last INCLUDED
  block range's MaxSeq (seg.Blocks[br.Last].MaxSeq). The §12.1 hazard: the next
  page's exclusive afterSeq = segment MaxSeq drops every un-included tail block
  of that segment forever (their MaxSeq <= the segment MaxSeq), so a
  collection/DID-filtered backfill silently loses the segment's later matched
  blocks.
expected-detection: |
  Killed by TestPartB_MidSegmentTruncation (#182, partb tier): the DID-filtered
  client paginates inside a single segment whose matched blocks are
  non-contiguous; reporting the segment MaxSeq skips the tail blocks, so the
  emitted seqs are missing the later matched blocks and diverge from ground
  truth. The manifest unit test TestPlanBackfill_MidSegmentCutCursorIsBlockMaxSeq
  also covers this directly, but the partb tier proves the end-to-end loss.
expected-tier: partb
tiers: partb

